{{Infobox person | name = Zach Woods | image = Zach Woods at SXSW 2016.jpg | caption = Woods at [[SXSW 2016]] | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|9|25|}}{{cite web|url=http://www.improvresourcecenter.com/mb/member.php?u=2114 |title=Improv Message Boards - View Profile: Zach W |publisher=Improvresourcecenter.com |date= |accessdate=2013-05-20}} | birth_place = [[Trenton, New Jersey]] | alma_mater = [[New York University]] | years_active = 2004–present | imagesize = }} '''Zach Woods''' (born September 25, 1984) is an American actor and comedian. He is best known for starring as Jared Dunn on the [[HBO]] comedy series ''[[Silicon Valley (TV series)|Silicon Valley]]''. Prior to that, he was a series regular for 3 seasons on the [[NBC]] sitcom ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]'', playing the role of [[Gabe Lewis]]. He also recurs on the HBO series ''[[Veep (TV series)|Veep]]'' and on the [[USA Network]] sitcom ''[[Playing House (TV series)|Playing House]]''. ==Early life== Woods was born in [[Trenton, New Jersey]].{{Cite news|url=http://www.lamag.com/culturefiles/meet-zach-woods-the-anxious-heart-of-silicon-valley/|title=Meet Zach Woods, the Anxious Heart of "Silicon Valley" - Los Angeles Magazine|date=2014-05-29|work=Los Angeles Magazine|access-date=2017-02-26|language=en-US}} He is Jewish.{{cite web|url=http://www.wtfpod.com/podcast/episodes/episode_597_-_zach_woods |title=Episode 597 - Zach Woods}} Woods' father is a trained psychiatrist and social worker who specializes in clinical therapy, and his mother is a nurse practitioner. As a child, he participated in both [[Karate]] and [[Little League Baseball]]. Woods is a middle child; he has an older brother and a younger sister. During 1997 and 1998, he also attended [[Interlochen Center for the Arts]] for summer camp.{{Cite news|url=http://crescendo.interlochen.org/story/and-nominee-interlochen-grammys-golden-globes-and-academy-awards|title=And the nominee is ... Interlochen at the Grammys, Golden Globes and Academy Awards}} Woods grew up in Yardley, Pennsylvania, and graduated from [[Pennsbury High School]] in 2003. He is a graduate of [[New York University]].{{Cite news|url=http://www.interviewmagazine.com/culture/zach-woods/|title=Zach Woods and Human Comedy|work=Interview Magazine|access-date=2017-02-26}} ==Career== [[File:Bobby Moynihan & Zach Woods, Del Close Marathon 2.09.jpg|thumb|Woods with [[Bobby Moynihan]] in 2015]] He started performing improv at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre]] at age 16 and was a part of the [[Improvisational comedy|improvisational]] sketch troupe "The Stepfathers", whose members also include [[Bobby Moynihan]] and [[Chris Gethard]].{{cite web|url=https://ucbtheatre.com/show/717 |title=The Stepfathers |publisher=Newyork.ucbtheatre.com |date= |accessdate=2013-05-20}} He has taught improv at [[Columbia University]], [[Duke University]] and Lincoln Center.{{cite web|title=UCB Theatre – Zach Woods|url=http://ucbcomedy.com/user/314}} He has appeared in such films as ''[[In the Loop]]'', ''[[The Other Guys]]'' and appeared in the [[CollegeHumor]] skit "Adam and Eve in the Friends Zone". Woods is also known for starring as Awkward Boy, the [[protagonist]] in the [[YouTube]] video series ''The Most Awkward Boy in the World''.{{cite web |url=http://www.ucbcomedy.com/talent/view/38/zach-woods |title=Zach Woods • UCB Comedy |publisher=Ucbcomedy.com |date= |accessdate=2013-05-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130708122646/http://www.ucbcomedy.com/talent/view/38/zach-woods |archivedate=July 8, 2013 |df=mdy-all }} In 2010, Woods appeared as a [[zombie]] in a [[Starburst (confectionery)|Starburst candy]] commercial.{{cite web |url=http://adweek.blogs.com/adfreak/30-freakiest-ads-of-2010.html |title=Starburst "Zombie" Commercial |author=Tim Nudd |date=December 1, 2010 |work=The 30 Freakiest Ads of 2010 |publisher=AdFreak.com |accessdate=February 6, 2011}} Starting in 2010, he portrayed [[Gabe Lewis]] on the [[National Broadcasting Company|NBC]] sitcom ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]''. He was promoted to series regular beginning in [[The Office (U.S. season 7)|Season 7]].{{cite web|url=http://ausiellofiles.ew.com/2010/06/16/office-promotes-zach-woods/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100618023611/http://ausiellofiles.ew.com/2010/06/16/office-promotes-zach-woods/|dead-url=yes|archive-date=June 18, 2010|title=Exclusive: 'The Office' promotes 'Gabe' to series regular|work=Entertainment Weekly's EW.com|date=June 16, 2010|accessdate=June 16, 2010}} Since 2014, Woods has costarred as Jared on [[HBO]]'s ''[[Silicon Valley (TV series)|Silicon Valley]]''. He also appeared on HBO's ''[[Veep (TV series)|Veep]]'' as Ed Webster. Woods had a role in the action comedy ''[[Spy (2015 film)|Spy]]'' (2015), alongside [[Melissa McCarthy]], [[Jason Statham]], [[Rose Byrne]], [[Jude Law]], [[Allison Janney]], and [[50 Cent]].{{Cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2014/05/adrian-lester-joins-grey-lady-zach-woods-cast-in-spy-723488/|title=Adrian Lester Joins ‘Grey Lady’; Zach Woods Cast In ‘Spy’|date=2014-05-02|work=Deadline|access-date=2017-02-26|language=en-US}} He appeared in Feig's follow-up movie ''[[Ghostbusters (2016 film)|Ghostbusters]]'' in 2016. ==Filmography== ===Film=== {| class="wikitable sortable" |- !
